Preheat the #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @butternut squash{1} then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Scoop out the seeds. Chop it into 2cm chunks. Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss to coat, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender and golden.

Meanwhile, pop the @cauliflower florets{300} onto another #tray{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, toss to coat, then roast on the middle shelf of your oven until tender and starting to char, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn both the veg halfway through cooking. In the meantime, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @green beans{80}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}.

Pop the tomatoes in a large #salad bowl{} and drizzle with @oil{}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} or #saucepan{} over medium heat. Once hot, stir in the shallot along with a pinch of @salt{}. Cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring frequently, then add the garlic. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add another drizzle of @oil{} to the pan.

Stir in the @plain flour{24g} to coat everything evenly. Cook for ~{30%seconds} then, gradually, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @water{250}(for the sauce). Add the @vegetable stock powder{1} and stir to dissolve. Bring to the boil, stirring constantly till smooth, then bubble until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Stir in the @dijon mustard{1/2} (careful, it's hot!) and the cheese until melted. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10}, @dried thyme{1/2} and @olive oil{1} for the topping into a small #bowl{}. Add a pinch of @salt{} and stir to combine. When the cauliflower and squash are ready, spoon them into the cheesy sauce and mix gently to combine. Transfer into an #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle over the herby breadcrumbs. Pop the dish onto the top shelf of the oven and cook until the the top is golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

In the meantime, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil. Once boiling add the green beans and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}, then drain in a #colander{} and set aside to cool slightly. When ready to serve, toss the green beans into the bowl with the tomatoes and mix to combine. Once the gratin is out of the oven, share between your plates with the green bean and tomato salad on the side. Enjoy!